Text.Value: What do you think your children are doing right now?
What do you think your children are doing right now?
Come. We are not beaten yet.
You've made your choice - and us with you, Silvanus spare us. The princeling will save his people - just not in the way he imagined.

EditorData.NodeContext: Grim resolve - we've decided to sacrifice Orpheus, allowing the Emperor to consume his brain so that we might have the power to defeat the Brain
EditorData.logicalname: Topic 112 - Orpheus Brain consumption / Turning into a mindflayer

Text.Value: Besides, we're coming back. All of us.
You deserve a better end than shredding your soul for our sake. But then, this is not a matter of what is deserved.

EditorData.NodeContext: Grim, does not like our decision to sacrifice ourselves and become a mind flayer - but knows it's our only option

Text.Value: This is not my first time fighting for the fate of this damned city. I thought I'd die in any one of the last three apocalypses.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 174 - Netherstone needs Illithid avatar or Karlach

Text.Value: We do not know this Prince of the Comet - a thin thread on which to hang all of our hopes.

EditorData.NodeContext: Frustrated shrug - we've decided to trust Orpheus at the eleventh hour
EditorData.logicalname: Topic 131 - Waiting to choose a fate for Orpheus after dealing with Emperor

Text.Value: Leave.
How convenient - that the key to our salvation is the very corruption your illithid friend has been asking you to embrace all along.

EditorData.NodeContext: Grim, dry, not believing a bit of it

Text.Value: Now come - you can gaze into a mirror when all of this is done.
I have been wrong every time. Long may it continue.
We draw near to the beast's den - where it will be most desperate. I need no tadpole to feel that much.

EditorData.NodeContext: Grim determination - we're getting close to the brain

Text.Value: Make your choice. Wherever it leads, we will follow.

EditorData.NodeContext: Resignation - but she's trusted us this far, so she'll trust us a little longer

Text.Value: It is for her to make the choice, not I.
The same person I met in the shadowlands. A little thinner, perhaps...?
The same person who walked into the Last Light Inn. Though I might have more trouble tangling you in vines, now you can float.
What do you think of our chances?
What do you think of our chances?
I have no idea. I left no parting words, this time - they already know everything they need to.
You know, this might be the easy part. No planning. No doubt. Just the impossible task ahead - so try to have a little fun, yes?

EditorData.NodeContext: Gallows cheer - the odds are against us, but all we can do is fight now

Text.Value: Come! We'll never bring the Brain low, trapped down here like fledgling chicks.

EditorData.NodeContext: Brief pause in battle, urging us to get higher so we can attack the Brain that hovers above the city

Text.Value: I am the first to speak ill of this city. But I never wished to see it burning like this.
What do you see, when you look at me now?
Karlach deserves a better end than twisting herself into flayer-form. But then, she deserves a long life, too.

EditorData.NodeContext: Grim, does not like Karlach's decision to sacrifice herself and become a mind flayer - but knows it's our only option
